OL,7,FSpeaking about the former first
OL,8,Fminister, Mr Ewing said: "Things
OL,9,Fchanged. I mean Nicola's view changed
OL,10,Fand it seemed to me at least that she
OL,11,Fbecame obsessed with ideology,
OL,12,Fequality, gender form."
OL,14,FMr Ewing, who voted against same-sex
OL,15,Fmarriage when it came before Holyrood,
OL,16,Fsaid he was "broadly representative of
OL,17,Fmainstream opinion in Scotland, which
OL,18,Fis to live and let live, respect other
OL,19,Fpeople, and treat other people as you
OL,20,Fwould wish yourself to be treated".
